cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NI 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it focuses on spiking neural networks and their performance on neuromorphic datasets. It also touches upon unsupervised learning, which is a common topic in this sub-category. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a likely sub-category as the paper analyzes the discriminative power of neuromorphic datasets, specifically N-MNIST, which is a dataset of handwritten digits. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also possible sub-categories as the paper discusses the performance of different machine learning algorithms on the dataset. 

Finally, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a less likely sub-category as it is not directly related to the content of the paper.
